Error: Common Minecraft Error: "Could Not Create The Java Virtual Machine" Error Message.

Step-By-Step

Solution: 1. Close Minecraft and any other programs currently running on your computer.
2. Open your Minecraft launcher, and click on "Edit Profile."
3. In the "Java Settings" section, ensure that the "Executable" option is set to "Java" and that the "JVM Arguments" field is empty.
4. If the field contains any text, delete it and click "Save
